#: ../../E/EOF.rst:5
msgid "EOF"
msgstr "EOF"

#: ../../E/EOF.rst:7
msgid "/E·O·F/, n\\."
msgstr "/E·O·F/, 名詞"

#: ../../E/EOF.rst:9
msgid "[abbreviation, ‘End Of File’]"
msgstr "[略語、‘End Of File’]"

#: ../../E/EOF.rst:12
msgid ""
"[techspeak] The :ref:`out-of-band` value returned by C's sequential "
"character-input functions (and their equivalents in other environments) when"
" end of file has been reached. This value is usually -1 under C libraries "
"postdating V6 Unix, but was originally 0. DOS hackers think EOF is ^Z, and a"
" few Amiga hackers think it's ^\\."
msgstr ""
"[techspeak] ファイルの終わりに達したときに、Cの逐次文字入力関数(および他の環境におけるその相当物)が返す\\ :ref:`out-of-"
"band`\\ な値。この値は、V6 "
"Unix以降のCライブラリでは通常-1だが、元々は0だった。DOSハッカーはEOFを^Zだと思っており、少数のAmigaハッカーは^\\\\だと思っている。"

#: ../../E/EOF.rst:17
msgid ""
"[Unix] The keyboard character (usually control-D, the ASCII EOT (End Of "
"Transmission) character) that is mapped by the terminal driver into an end-"
"of-file condition."
msgstr ""
"[Unix] 端末ドライバによってファイル終端の状態にマッピングされるキーボード文字(通常はcontrol-D、ASCIIのEOT(End Of "
"Transmission)文字)。"

#: ../../E/EOF.rst:20
msgid ""
"Used by extension in non-computer contexts when a human is doing something "
"that can be modeled as a sequential read and can't go further. \"Yeah, I "
"looked for a list of 360 mnemonics to post as a joke, but I hit EOF pretty "
"fast; all the library had was a :ref:`JCL` manual.\" See also :ref:`EOL`\\."
msgstr ""
"人間が逐次読み込みとしてモデル化できる何かを行っていて、それ以上先に進めないとき、コンピューター以外の文脈でも拡張的に使われる。「そうだ、ジョークとして投稿しようと360のニーモニック一覧を探したんだが、すぐにEOFに当たっちまったよ。図書館にあったのは\\"
" :ref:`JCL`\\ のマニュアルだけだった。」\\ :ref:`EOL`\\ も参照。"
